@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowColor #2F4F4F
skinparam DefaultTextAlignment center

left to right direction

title S6 Integrated Architecture for Dual-Master Defense

actor "Legitimate User" as User
actor "Adversarial Client" as Attacker

cloud "Edge Zone" {
  component "C1 Gateway Layer\nNGINX / Istio GW / Kong" as Gateway
  component "C4 Rate Limiter\nIngress annotations\nmoderate/strict" as RL
}

cloud "Service Trust Zone" {
  component "C2 Service Mesh\nIstio mTLS or Linkerd mTLS" as Mesh

  node "realistic namespace" {
    component "auth-service\nPOST /login\nJWT issue" as Auth
    component "api-service\nGET /profile\nGET /users" as Api
    component "data-service\nDB access" as Data
    database "PostgreSQL\napp_users" as DB
  }

  component "C3 Network Policies\nbasic/moderate/strict" as NetPol
}

cloud "Observability and Analysis Zone" {
  component "k6 S6 Flow\nnormal + attack" as K6
  component "Prometheus\nCPU/Mem scrape" as Prom
  component "S6 Analyzer\n6 metrics + security traces" as Analyzer
  artifact "S6 Raw NDJSON\nrandomized_campaigns" as Raw
  artifact "S6 Integrated CSV\nscaling_tests" as Csv
}

User --> Gateway : HTTPS requests
Attacker --> Gateway : attack probes\ninvalid creds / unauth access

Gateway --> RL : enforce edge rate limits
RL --> Auth : allow/limit
RL --> Api : allow/limit

Gateway --> Mesh : routed traffic
Mesh --> Auth : mTLS S2S
Mesh --> Api : mTLS S2S
Api --> Data : authorized call
Data --> DB : SQL read/list

NetPol -[hidden]-> Auth
NetPol -[hidden]-> Api
NetPol -[hidden]-> Data
NetPol .. Auth : ingress/egress rules
NetPol .. Api : ingress/egress rules
NetPol .. Data : ingress/egress rules

K6 --> Gateway : scenario execution\nVUs 1/5/10/20\nmode normal/attack
Prom --> Auth : resource telemetry
Prom --> Api : resource telemetry
Prom --> Data : resource telemetry
Prom --> DB : resource telemetry

K6 --> Raw : per-run NDJSON output
Prom --> Analyzer : query_range data
Raw --> Analyzer : latency/error/rps\nlogin/users/JWT traces
Analyzer --> Csv : integrated metrics output

note bottom of Analyzer
S6 integrated output includes:
- avg_ms, p95_ms, err_pct, rps
- cpu_mcores, mem_mib
- login_ok, users_ok
- jwt_trace_events, unique_jwt_fp
- profile_db_latency_ms_avg
- users_db_latency_ms_avg
end note

@enduml
